cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the performance of ultra-dense networks in the presence of both LOS and NLOS signal propagation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper studies the Area Spectral Efficiency (ASE) of UDNs. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper discusses the energy efficiency of UDNs. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper uses a stochastic geometry-based model to analyze the performance of UDNs. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely as the paper does not focus on security or cryptography.
